---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import KaTeX from "../../components/KaTeX.astro";
const title = "Beautiful Mathematical Notation on the Web";
const description = "Implementing LaTeX-style mathematical equations in web content using KaTeX and modern markdown processors.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-8">
    <header class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Beautiful Mathematical Notation on the Web</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Implementing LaTeX-style mathematical equations in web content using KaTeX and modern markdown processors.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="max-w-none">
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Mathematical notation on the web has come a long way. With tools like KaTeX, we can now render beautiful LaTeX-style equations.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Why KaTeX?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        KaTeX is a fast, self-contained JavaScript library for rendering math notation. 
        It's faster than MathJax and produces consistent, high-quality output across all browsers.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Basic Examples</h2>
      
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-6 mb-3">Famous Equations</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Einstein's mass-energy equivalence:</p>
      <KaTeX expression="E = mc^2" displayMode={true} />
      
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Euler's identity, often called the most beautiful equation in mathematics:</p>
      <KaTeX expression="e^{i\pi} + 1 = 0" displayMode={true} />
      
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The Pythagorean theorem:</p>
      <KaTeX expression="a^2 + b^2 = c^2" displayMode={true} />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-6 mb-3">Calculus</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The definition of a derivative:</p>
      <KaTeX expression="f'(x) = \\lim_{h \\to 0} \\frac{f(x+h) - f(x)}{h}" displayMode={true} />
      
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">A definite integral:</p>
      <KaTeX expression="\\int_a^b f(x) \\, dx" displayMode={true} />
      
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">The fundamental theorem of calculus:</p>
      <KaTeX expression="\\int_a^b f'(x) \\, dx = f(b) - f(a)" displayMode={true} />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-6 mb-3">Linear Algebra</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Matrix multiplication:</p>
      <KaTeX expression="\\begin{bmatrix} a & b \\\\ c & d \\end{bmatrix} \\begin{bmatrix} x \\\\ y \\end{bmatrix} = \\begin{bmatrix} ax + by \\\\ cx + dy \\end{bmatrix}" displayMode={true} />
      
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Eigenvalue equation:</p>
      <KaTeX expression="A\\mathbf{v} = \\lambda\\mathbf{v}" displayMode={true} />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-6 mb-3">Statistics</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Normal distribution probability density function:</p>
      <KaTeX expression="f(x) = \\frac{1}{\\sigma\\sqrt{2\\pi}} e^{-\\frac{1}{2}\\left(\\frac{x-\\mu}{\\sigma}\\right)^2}" displayMode={true} />
      
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Bayes' theorem:</p>
      <KaTeX expression="P(A|B) = \\frac{P(B|A)P(A)}{P(B)}" displayMode={true} />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-6 mb-3">Inline Math</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        You can also include math inline, like <KaTeX expression="x = \\frac{-b \\pm \\sqrt{b^2 - 4ac}}{2a}" displayMode={false} /> 
        for the quadratic formula, or <KaTeX expression="\\sum_{i=1}^n i = \\frac{n(n+1)}{2}" displayMode={false} /> 
        for the sum of first n natural numbers.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Advanced Features</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        KaTeX supports complex mathematical notation including:
      </p>
      
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-6 mb-3">Complex Fractions</h3>
      <KaTeX expression="\\frac{\\frac{a}{b}}{\\frac{c}{d}} = \\frac{ad}{bc}" displayMode={true} />
      
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-6 mb-3">Summations and Products</h3>
      <KaTeX expression="\\sum_{k=0}^{n} \\binom{n}{k} x^k y^{n-k} = (x+y)^n" displayMode={true} />
      
      <KaTeX expression="\\prod_{i=1}^{n} x_i = x_1 \\cdot x_2 \\cdot \\ldots \\cdot x_n" displayMode={true} />
      
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-6 mb-3">Greek Letters and Symbols</h3>
      <KaTeX expression="\\alpha, \\beta, \\gamma, \\Delta, \\Theta, \\Lambda, \\Sigma, \\Omega" displayMode={true} />
      
      <KaTeX expression="\\forall x \\in \\mathbb{R}, \\exists y \\in \\mathbb{N} : x < y" displayMode={true} />
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .math.inline {
    display: inline;
  }
  
  .math.display {
    display: block;
    text-align: center;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
</style>